criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients with sepsis who meet the Sepsis 3.0 standard proposed by the 2016
             International Sepsis Expert Consensus, that is, for patients with infection or
             suspected infection, when sepsis-related sequential organ failure (Sequential
             (Sepsis-related) Organ Failure) Assessment (SOFA) score increased by ≥ 2 points from
             the baseline can be diagnosed as sepsis;

          2. It is estimated that the patient's ICU stay ≥24 hours;

          3. Obtain informed consent and sign an informed consent form.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. The patient's ICU hospital stay is less than 24 hours;

          2. Participated in other clinical research;

          3. Failed to sign the informed consent form.
